article.headline: Georgia St 79, William & Mary 70
article.story: ATLANTA (AP) -- Malcolm Manier and Herman Favors scored 18 points apeice to lead Georgia State to a 79-70 victory over William & Mary on Saturday. The Panthers (4-10, 2-5 Colonial Athletic Association) built a 36-20 lead at halftime, then pushed their advantage to 19 points twice in the second half. The Tribe (5-10, 0-6) responded with a 16-4 run over a five minute span. Corey Cofield scored five straight points and Nathan Mann made three consecutive 3-pointers, cutting the lead to 51-45 with 10:30 left in the game. After Georgia State pushed its lead back to 13, William & Mary trimmed the margin down to six with 1:11 remaining. But the Panthers responded with free throws to finish the win. Rahsad Chase scored 15 points and Boyd Copeland added 13 for Georgia State. Mann led William & Mary with 21 points off the bench. Cofied had 12 points and eight rebounds.
